toki
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the Maori adze or axe, originally of stone; an axe or tomahawk. [Maori]


Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Williams 433 Toki (i) ... <i>Adze or axe </i>generally made of stone, possibly sometimes of shell.: early spg <i>e-to-ki, tochee, toghee, togie, tokee tokey, </i>
